# Implementation Plan - Student Dashboard Transition & Test Conduct Fixes

The goal is to resolve issues in the new Livewire-based student test conduct and completely remove legacy Controller-based student dashboard components to ensure a clean, modern codebase.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The legacy student routes (prefixed with `/old`) will be completely removed. Any users currently using those routes will need to use the new dashboard at `/student`.

> [!WARNING]
> We will delete the `DashboardController`, `ExamsController`, and `StudentPlanController` under `App\Http\Controllers\Student`. Ensure no other parts of the system (like Admin or Franchise) depend on these specific student controllers.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Fix Test Conduct (Livewire)

#### [MODIFY] [OnlineTestRunner.php](file:///mnt/WebliesNew/test-and-notes-upgrading/app/Livewire/Student/Tests/OnlineTestRunner.php)
-   Update `loadQuestionsStructure` to filter out deleted pivot records (respecting `deleted_at`).
-   Add an `agreedToTerms` property and logic to prevent starting without agreement.
-   Refine the `saveAndNext` logic to handle the transition to the Review screen more gracefully.

#### [MODIFY] [online-test-runner.blade.php](file:///mnt/WebliesNew/test-and-notes-upgrading/resources/views/livewire/student/tests/online-test-runner.blade.php)
-   Enforce the "I agree to all instructions and terms" checkbox by wiring it to Livewire state.
-   Improve the Question Palette:
    -   Add global question numbers (1 to Total).
    -   Add color coding for "Not Visited" (Gray), "Visited but not Attempted" (Red), and "Attempted" (Green).
    -   Allow switching between all sections from the palette.
-   Improve the Review view summary layout.

